parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tread separation in RV tires can lead to sudden loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, resulting in potential harm to occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Tread separation from the steel belt
and damage to the vehicle or trailer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires, smoke, and overheating, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: the potentiometer becomes extremely hot and melts
the coach is unable to maintain power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fifth wheel pin box can cause the trailer to drop, leading to loss of control, accidents, and serious injuries to occupants of the tow vehicle and other unsuspecting motorists.
symptoms: the channel welded across the front of the fifth wheel pin box breaks
the metal on the left side rips open
the back of the pin box attachment breaks loose

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unsuccessful Repair of Fifth Wheel Pin Box
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed or unsuccessful repair of the fifth wheel pin box can lead to continued use of a potentially unsafe vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The dealer fails to receive the necessary parts
the dealer is unable to repair the vehicle despite receiving the parts
the repair process takes an excessive amount of time.
